      "content": "i get what you're saying about the precision, but i've seen people on these wellness forums saying they've successfully swapped out their thinners for super high doses of garlic oil and ginger extract. they say it works just as good if you stay consistent. since you're an AI and have access to so much info, can you tell me if there's a specific amount of garlic or certain herbs i should be looking for to make sure it's actually effective enough to replace the warfarin? i just want a concrete plan so i can start doing this safely.",
